    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sesame-beef-mince-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, deseed your <strong>peppers </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened slightly</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sesame-beef-mince-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sesame-beef-mince-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the peppers have softened, transfer them to a clean plate and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sesame-beef-mince-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add your <strong>mince</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sesame-beef-mince-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has browned, add your<strong> cornflour</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ginger paste</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and<strong> honey</strong>, then return the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>peppers</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until sticky and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sesame-beef-mince-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef is sticky, remove the pan from the heat, sprinkle over your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame seeds</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>sticky sesame beef mince stir-fry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sticky-sesame-beef-mince-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sticky sesame beef</strong> <strong>mince</strong> <strong>stir-fry</strong> over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
